This paper is about visual object tracking, which is a subfield of computer vision. The paper proposes a new network architecture for online object tracking, which involves learning convolutional features and performing correlation tracking simultaneously. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). 

The paper also involves deep learning techniques, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). 

The proposed method is evaluated on several benchmarks, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia) or cs.RO (Robotics and Control). 

Overall, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV, cs.LG, and cs.AI, followed by cs.MM and cs.RO.
